VALUES ('fc427e53-3cbc-4c6c-a72a-6cbcdee17a61', 'The author of Text 2 would most likely criticize Text 1 for which of the following?', 'Text 1
In 2009, urban economist Dr. Elena Park argued that municipal parks chiefly benefit residents who engage in vigorous exercise, treating caloric expenditure as the sole measurable outcome of green-space investment. Policy memos recommended funding athletic courts while de-emphasizing passive seating because residents who did not exercise received negligible returns in her model. Critics noted reliance on self-reported activity logs rather than clinical biomarkers. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. Follow-up work will test whether the pattern holds across additional sites and populations.

Text 2
A 2025 industry analysis found factories adopting collaborative robots often reclassified rather than eliminated roles, with technicians maintaining cells and logistics staff managing reconfigured lines. Productivity rose gradually over four years, and headcount at studied plants remained within five percent of pre-automation levels. Managers ranked task redesign as more decisive than the robots themselves. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. Follow-up work will test whether the pattern holds across additional', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"By conceding that Text 1''s strawman accurately represents all opposing views, though Text 2 supplies alternative mechanisms Text 1 overlooks throughout","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Mutual Consensus Decoy] Claims Text 2 agrees with a claim Text 2 actually rejects or qualifies."},{"id":"B","text":"By claiming Text 2 abandons the shared topic entirely, treating a methodological dispute as proof the texts address unrelated disciplines overall in sum.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Scope Creep] Attributes an extreme generalized position beyond either text''s guarded assertions."},{"id":"C","text":"By comparing the texts'' citation counts, an external metric neither author uses to evaluate the validity of the competing claims in sum.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Out-of-Bound Contrast] Contrasts the texts on a variable neither author discusses."},{"id":"D","text":"By broadening Text 1''s theoretical frame because Text 2 links outcomes to conditions Text 1''s model omits yet does not deny entirely.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (D). Correct (D). This choice captures how Text 2 responds to Text 1''s claim without overstating agreement or inventing variables neither text mentions."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Step 1 — Summarize each text
Focus on {{yellow:activity}} in the passage. The cross text response item asks you to summarize each text before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Compare the perspectives
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On hard items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Choose the best response
Choice D is correct: By broadening Text 1''s theoretical frame because Text 2 links outcomes to conditions Text 1''s model omits yet does not deny entirely..

Distractor analysis:
- A: [Mutual Consensus Decoy] Claims Text 2 agrees with a claim Text 2 actually rejects or qualifies.
- B: [Scope Creep] Attributes an extreme generalized position beyond either text''s guarded assertions.
- C: [Out-of-Bound Contrast] Contrasts the texts on a variable neither author discusses.', NULL, 'Craft and Structure', 'Cross-Text Connections', 'reading_writing', 'craft', 'CTC', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"rw_subtype":"cross_text_response","rw_format":"text_1_text_2","generator":"regenerate-english-fresh.mjs","regen_seed_offset":100000,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now());
